  "text": "and CDc from GSE16879. These datasets contain biopsy gene expression profiles generated from 2 cohorts of UC patients (Cohort A and B in GSE14580 and GSE12251 respectively), and 1 cohort of CD patients (part of GSE16879). They were originally designed for the discovery of gene signatures that can predict, at baseline, if a patient is likely to respond to an anti-TNFα treatment (Infliximab) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In terms of signatures, all signatures were identified from baseline gene expression differential analysis between responders and non-responders to Infliximab treatment in the same set of 3 IBD cohorts of UC (cohorts UC-A and UC-B) or CD (cohort CDc) patients [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , exception being the IRRAT signature which, subsequent to the study it originated with, was found to correlate with anti-TNFα response at baseline in the UC-B cohort [CITATION_5] . In addition, we obtained blood gene expression data of IBD patients for whom endoscopic activity was available (GSEXXX) [REF] , in which we assessed the relation of the CCL7-CCR2-TREM1 axis to monitor disease activity.",
